title: For Sale:  Winchester Model 12 Featherweight 12 ga.
postcontent: Winchester Model 12 Featherweight pump action 12 gauge shotgun in excellent condition.  This does not have a vented rib.  It is a full choke, 28" barrel.  It is in better condition that nearly any Model 12 I have seen.  The Featherweights were only made for one year according to some reading I did.  It was made in 1961 according to one serial number lookup, however, another lookup said it was only made from March 1959 through March 1960.  Model 12 production overall ceased in 1963 due to high production (machining) costs.  Stamped guns were quicker and cheaper to make.  Regardless, it will be a special acquisition for somebody, at a terriffic price.

title: For Sale:  ELCAN M145 and Vortex for Sale or Trade
postcontent:
For sale or trade are a Vortex Strikefire $120, and four ELCAN M145 5.56 combat optics. One of the ELCAN is like new and I have three others in Excellent to very good condition. I picked the ELCANs up at a government auction and the and Vortex I’m not using. They are 100% genuine article.
The M145 Telescope is a fixed 3.4 power, 28mm optical sight that has been designed to engage targets accurately out to 1200m range. The optical sight weighs 24 oz. (681 gr) and is extremely rugged for rough field conditions. The sight has an 8.2mm diameter exit pupil, which provides excellent vision in low light levels, i.e. dawn and dusk, and also for rapid target acquisition. The zeroing adjustment increments in both windage and elevation are 2.5 mm at 10 meters range for each detent (click of movement) and 5 inches at 500 meter range. The mount is designed to fit to the Picatinny rail MIL.Std. 1913. The optical sight has an eye relief of approximately 3 inches (70mm). Eye relief is the distance between the eye and the sight’s rear eyepiece lens. The reticle pattern has built-in trajectory compensation from 300m to 1200m range. The reticle is illuminated, by a battery. It has been used in conflicts around the world and is rated for the heaviest of machineguns, such as the M249, 240G, and MINIMI and of course M16 type rifles. This optic compares favorably against anything Leupold, Aimpoint, ACOG, or EO Tech puts out!
I’m interested in UZI, UC 9mm, Sten guns (Not Parts), Keltec Sub-2000 that takes .40 Glock 23 Magazines, Keltec SU-16, Keltec KSG, Browning Hi-Power in 9mm or clones, M1-Carbine, M1 Garand, M1A and M14 clones, AK 47 rifles or pistols, Marlin Camp Carbine in .45, Six shot Ruger and S&W revolvers in .357, PAP, Thompson .45 carbines, PSL, Hi-Power in 9mm, factory assembled AR-15, M16, Kimber 1911 in .45acp, Colt 1911, Mossberg 930 tactical shotguns, shockwave 590 shotgun and other quality firearms.( I don’t want your Parts AR, Hi-Point, Taurus, Glock or other plastic pistol) I don’t hunt, so no Fudd guns.
The prices are negotiable for the ELCAN optics the other two are firm. If the AD is up the optic is available. I’ll trade for firearms and not for your electronics, gold, jewelry, golf clubs or other non-gun things. I’m not desperate so please no lowballs. Make me an offer the worst I can say is no thanks. My number is 83o-221-o417. I prefer texts and I can send additional pictures on request. I’m willing to meet halfway within reason that means no Dallas, Laredo or Houston or some other nonsense (I’m in Schertz)! That means in a public area (Wal-Mart, Academy, HEB etc.…) between San Antonio and Cabela’s in Buda. If you want to look at it first I’ll be more then glad to show it to you at the Wal-Mart in Schertz and not half-way. I don’t ship and we meet face to face Cash no checks during daylight hours. If you want paperwork I’ll be glad to meet at an FFL and do the transfer on your dime. All pertinent laws will be followed and you will need a TX ID, CHL or LTC is preferred for firearm swaps. Folks I’m easy to get along with and will show you the same amount of respect you show me. 5.56 .223, 7.62x39 7.62x51 .357

title: For Sale:  NEW IN BOX POLISH PPS43-C Pistol 7.62x25 with (4) 35rd Mags
postcontent: Polish PPS43-C Pistol 7.62x25 with (4) 35rd Mags The History... The PPS43 (Pistolet-Pulemet Sudaeva, model of 1943 = Sudaev submachine gun) was born as an answer for the need of a weapon that would be more compact and mobile than the PPSh-41, which was in use then by the Soviet Army. The PPSh-41 was somewhat too long to be used by tank crews, mobile recon groups and paratroopers. In late 1941, the Red Army issued a request for a new, more compact SMG. Designer Sudaev initially designed his new SMG in 1942 and it was adopted under the designation of PPS42. The next year he refined the design and this final model was designated as PPS43. This SMG was manufactured in significant numbers, with nearly 2 million PPS43 weapons manufactured between 1943 and 1946. The PPS43 is sometimes referred to as the best SMG of World War II. After WWII, it was widely exported to pro-Soviet regimes around the world and widely copied. The PPS43 was license-produced in Poland starting in 1946. Today... Pioneer Arms has redesigned this historical firearm to shoot from a closed bolt position. The safety is located at the front of the trigger guard. The receiver and barrel shroud are made from stamped steel. The rear sight is an L-shaped flip type and is marked for 100 and 200 meter distance. The front sight is a fixed blade. The barrel is equipped with a simple muzzle brake. This firearm is an ATF approved pistol. The stock has no function and is permanently fixed in its folded, closed position. This pistol is manufactured at the famed Radom Plant in Poland by Pioneer Arms. All parts and components are Polish made. The PPS43-C pistol comes with a curved box magazine which holds up to 35 rounds. Specifications  Model: PPS43-C Type: Semi-auto sporting pistol Weight: 6.7 lb. empty; 8.1 lb. loaded with 35rd magazine Overall length: 24.2" Barrel length: 9.8" Cartridge: 7.62x25mm Tokarev Action: Closed bolt, semi-auto Muzzle velocity: Approximately 1,640 ft/s Effective range: 100m Maximum range: 200m Feed system: 35rd detachable box magazine - (4) included Sights: Flip rear sight; fixed blade front sight
